responded: The use-after-free is triggered because `dom_perform_xinclude` (called from `zim_DOMDocument_xinclude`) frees or invalidates the document node(s), but the `intern->ptr` in the associated `dom_object` is not set to `NULL`. Later, when the object is destructed via `dom_objects_free_storage`, it attempts to access the already-freed memory, causing a use-after-free.

The correct fix is to set `intern->ptr = NULL` in `dom_perform_xinclude` after the xinclude operation, since the document node may have been freed or replaced. This prevents double-free/use-after-free in the object destructor.

Let's prepare the patch.

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 5bbe99eb364..bdc12f47e78 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1727,6 +1727,9 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long fl

 	php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);

+	/* Prevent use-after-free: if the document node was replaced/freed, clear the pointer */
+	intern->ptr = NULL;
+
 	return err;
 }

