responded: The previous patch set `intern->ptr = NULL` unconditionally, which is not correct because the pointer should only be cleared if the document node is actually replaced or freed by `xmlXIncludeProcessFlags`. Setting it to NULL always could break valid references.

The use-after-free occurs because after `xmlXIncludeProcessFlags`, the document node may be replaced or freed, but `intern->ptr` still points to the old memory. To fix this, we should check if the node pointer in `intern->ptr` is still valid (i.e., matches `docp`), and if not, set `intern->ptr = NULL`.

Let's update the patch accordingly: after the xinclude process, if `intern->ptr` is non-NULL and its node pointer does not match the current `docp`, set `intern->ptr = NULL`.

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 5bbe99eb364..5e884665889 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1727,6 +1727,11 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long fl

 	php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);

+	/* If the document node was replaced/freed, clear the pointer to avoid use-after-free */
+	if (intern->ptr != NULL && ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node != (xmlNodePtr)docp) {
+		intern->ptr = NULL;
+	}
+
 	return err;
 }

