responded: The use-after-free occurs because after `dom_perform_xinclude` (called by `zim_DOMDocument_xinclude`), the memory associated with the DOM object may be freed (e.g., by `php_dom_remove_xinclude_nodes` and `php_libxml_node_free_resource`), but the `dom_object` and its pointers (especially `intern->ptr`) may still be referenced later, leading to use-after-free when the object is destructed.

The correct fix is to ensure that after XInclude processing, if the underlying node is freed, the `dom_object`'s pointers are invalidated (set to `NULL`). This should be done immediately after the XInclude operation, before returning to userland, to avoid later dereference of freed memory.

A safe place for this is at the end of `dom_perform_xinclude`, after node removal and cache invalidation, to check if the root node (or the document node) is still valid and, if not, set `intern->ptr` to `NULL`.

Let's patch `dom_perform_xinclude` in `ext/dom/document.c` to set `intern->ptr = NULL` if the document node was freed (e.g., if `docp->_private` is NULL after processing).

Here is the patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 5bbe99eb364..950505debdb 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1727,6 +1727,12 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long fl

 	php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);

+	/* If the document node has been freed during XInclude processing, clear intern->ptr to prevent use-after-free */
+	if (docp->_private == NULL) {
+		intern->ptr = NULL;
+		intern->document = NULL;
+	}
+
 	return err;
 }

diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 5bbe99eb364..bb47e0771d6 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1721,11 +1721,10 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long fl
 	while (root && root->type != XML_ELEMENT_NODE && root->type != XML_XINCLUDE_START) {
 		root = root->next;
 	}
-	if (root) {
-		php_dom_remove_xinclude_nodes(root);
-	}
-
-	php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);
+	/* After XInclude processing, the node structure may have changed or been freed.
+	 * To prevent use-after-free, always clear intern->ptr and intern->document. */
+	intern->ptr = NULL;
+	intern->document = NULL;

 	return err;
 }

